00:44:07.932 --> 00:44:11.792
really define this disease. And then the timeframe from an in situ

732
00:44:11.812 --> 00:44:15.712
carcinoma STIC lesion to an invasive cancer is about 6.5 years, which is

733
00:44:15.752 --> 00:44:19.472
a number that's been verified at least in two independent

734
00:44:19.552 --> 00:44:23.512
studies. Unfortunately, once these cancers make it to the ovary, it progresses

735
00:44:23.572 --> 00:44:26.572
rather rapidly to involve the peritoneal cavity within one to two years.

736
00:44:28.492 --> 00:44:30.552
Now, the implications of this, you already heard about, right?

737
00:44:30.672 --> 00:44:32.352
SEAFM protocol is important, right?

738
00:44:32.432 --> 00:44:35.392
That should be used in the assessment of all risk-reducing surgeries.

739
00:44:35.972 --> 00:44:39.892
Opportunistic salpingectomy is already proving out to be an incredible

740
00:44:39.952 --> 00:44:42.432
tool for reducing the incidence of ovarian cancer.

741
00:44:42.452 --> 00:44:46.262
And then for the high-risk individuals of the BRCA1 and 2 mutations,

742
00:44:46.692 --> 00:44:49.942
this is being explored through three international clinical

743
00:44:50.052 --> 00:44:54.042
trials. You heard about WISP and tuba2, the NRG study here in

744
00:44:54.092 --> 00:44:56.912
the US, and the Protector UK study in the UK.

745
00:44:58.132 --> 00:45:01.792
So I wish you could stop here and say that isn't it great we

746
00:45:01.932 --> 00:45:05.672
found out where this cancer comes from, and now we have changed the way we think

747
00:45:05.752 --> 00:45:09.542
about prevention, right? Salpingectomy, and pat ourselves on the back.

748
00:45:09.971 --> 00:45:11.652
But as usual, things are never that simple.

749
00:45:11.712 --> 00:45:13.351
I'm going to illustrate this with a few cases.

750
00:45:13.372 --> 00:45:17.092
So here's a 46-year-old female patient with a BRCA1

751
00:45:17.132 --> 00:45:19.332
mutation, comes in for risk-reducing surgery.

752
00:45:20.652 --> 00:45:24.562
Pre-menopausal, CA125 ultrasound are normal, but she is found

753
00:45:24.612 --> 00:45:27.742
